The great majority of hemistichia clearly indicate a pause: sometimes at the end of a speech or a nar- rative, occasionally introducing one. These merely show that the poet was glad of an opportunity to rest the reader’s (or listener’s) ear from that mono- tony of the hexameter which is more apparent in Latin than Greek, and needs, as Virgil knew only too well, every possible artistic device to secure variety.
